    "body": "## Problem\r\n`vim.keymap.*.Opts.buf` allows `boolean` aliases for more widely used `integer?` values, `true` -> `0` and `false` -> `nil`. This conversion is unnecessary and can be handled at call sites.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nAs a follow-up to deprecating the `buffer` option (#38360), drop support for boolean values for the new `buf` option. The deprecated `buffer` continues to support booleans for backward compatibility.",
